==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: erysipelas
<hw>er`y*sip"e*las</hw> <pr>(⟦ecr⟧r`⟦icr⟧*s⟦icr⟧p"⟦esl⟧*l⟦ait⟧s)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr. Gr. <grk>'erysi`pelas</grk>;
<grk>'eryqro`s</grk> red + <grk>pe`lla</grk> hide, skin. See
<er>Red</er>, and <er>Pell</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>St. Anthony's fire; a febrile disease accompanied with a diffused
red edematous inflammation of the skin, which, starting usually from a
single point, spreads gradually over its surface. It is often
accompanied by severe constitutional symptoms. It is caused by a group A
hemolytic streptococcus (<spn>Streptococcus pyogenes</spn>), is
contagious, and formerly often occurred epidemically.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Erysipelatoid</ent>⟦br⟧
